The paper deals with the problem of computing an approximate saddle point for a convex-concave function over two bounded convex sets, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves sampling from log-concave distributions over the convex sets, which is a topic in computational geometry and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from convex analysis and optimization (cs.CC), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and machine learning (cs.LG) to analyze and implement the algorithm.
